COVID-19 Deaths in Europe - changes in weekly values

The information comes from the Johns Hopkins Coronavirus Resource Center Johns Hopkins Coronavirus Resource Center

The number of deaths in the previous two weeks is used to calculate if the rate is increasing or decreasing.

For example on the 8th February 2021 there had been a total of 1792 deaths in Belarus, on the 1st there were 1727 and on the 25th January there were 1658, so on the 8th the number in last week was 64 the number in the previous week was 70 a decrease of 8.6%.

If you hold your mouse over a cell the figures for the previous two weeks and the percentage increase is shown


Last updated on 31-Mar-2021 at 09:27:12
